## [CSS Transforms](http://learn.shayhowe.com/advanced-html-css/css-transforms/)

1. What does a CSS transform allow the developer to do to an element?
      * it allows images to be trnaformed on either a 2d or 3d plane
2. Provide an example of a transform and how you could see that being used on a website.
      * maybe an interactive logo where the companies logo is spinning at the top of the page. OR a logo that goes from 2d to 3d when hovered over.

[CSS Transitions & Animations](http://learn.shayhowe.com/advanced-html-css/transitions-animations/)

1. What does a CSS transition allow the developer to do to an element?
      * this allows an element to change from one line of code to another. this could be a color change a fade in and our effect or somehting much more complicated.
2. How does a CSS animation differ from a CSS transition?


